msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Complete copy of the Qur'ān with three sets of dual-page illuminated page surrounds. One page is copied twice, once upside down with a mostly blank facing page; there is no text missing.

supportDesc.extent: 333, ii leaves : 291 x 183 (215 x 115) mm bound to 287 x 210 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Unfoliated; catchwords on every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 15 long lines with border rules.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Sūrah titles in red ink, framed in gold; textblock ruled in two lines and red and one of black; gold roundels at end of each verse; readings marked in red; text partitions noted in the margins in red; double page illuminated text surrounds in red, white and black (f. [1]v-[2]r, [168]v-[169]r, [332]v-[333]r).

binding.p: Brown leather over pasteboard with flap on the front cover (Type II); stamped with blind stamped central mandorla, pendants, cornerpieces, frame, and border; plain paper doublure.

origin.p: The item is undated and unsigned; possibly 18th or 19th century.

history.provenance: Purchased from Bloomsbury, Friday 30 October 2020, lot 84.

surface.n: Fore edge flap closed, inside front cover
